# Hashing, Encryption and Decryption

This is a very common interview topic.

---

## Hashing

Hashing converts data into a fixed-length value.

Example:

```text
Password
   │
   ▼
Hash Function
   │
   ▼
8d969eef6ecad3...
```

### Characteristics

- One-way process
- Cannot be reversed
- Used for storing passwords securely

### Common Algorithms

- BCrypt  (Recommended)
- Argon2 
- SHA-256 (Not recommended alone for passwords)

### Password Storage

```text
User Password
      │
      ▼
BCrypt Hash
      │
      ▼
Stored in Database
```

---

## Encryption

Encryption converts readable data into unreadable data using a key.

Example:

```text
Hello
   │
   ▼
Encryption
   │
   ▼
jf82jsn3js...
```

### Purpose

- Protect sensitive information
- Data can be converted back using the correct key

---

## Decryption

Decryption converts encrypted data back into its original form.

Example:

```text
Encrypted Data
      │
      ▼
Decryption
      │
      ▼
Hello
```

---

# Difference Between Hashing and Encryption

| Hashing                    | Encryption                        |
|----------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| One-way process            |  Two-way process                  |
| Cannot be reversed         | Can be reversed using a key       |
| Used for storing passwords | Used for secure data transmission |
| No decryption required     | Requires decryption               |

